  "text": "Since V • is aCech resolution of X, we have Q tr (V • ) ∼ = Q tr (X) by [MVW, Proposition 6.12] . This proves the result. Proof. We can assume that F is connected. By 3.3 we get a sequence of blow-ups with smooth centers π : F ′ → F such that F ′ has (quasi)-projective coarse moduli space. By 3.6 M (F ) is a direct summand of M (F ′ ). By [CITATION_1] Theorem 1] there exists a smooth (quasi)-projective variety X and a finite flat morphism g : X → F ′ . Hence M (F ′ ) is a direct summand of M (X) which proves our claim. ",
